= f.label :name, "Name"
.input-row
  = f.text_field :name
.form-hint
  Typically this will be your company name

= f.label :locale_id, "The account locality", :class => 'spacer'
.input-row
  = select(:company, "locale_id", [[ 'Select a locale...', nil ]].concat(Locale.order("position").map { |p| [ p.name, p.id ] }) )
.form-hint
  We use this to ensure currency amounts and formatting is accurate to your locality.

= f.label :default_rate, "Default rate", :class => 'spacer'
.input-row
  = f.text_field :default_rate
.form-hint
  The rate per day you charge (do not use a currency symbol i.e. enter 800 for $800 per day)

= f.label :default_velocity, "Default velocity", :class => 'spacer'
.input-row
  = f.text_field :default_velocity
.form-hint
  The velocity is the average number of points you complete in a day